WEBVTT

1
00:00:15.210 --> 00:00:16.045
[woman] <i>Previously...</i>

2
00:00:16.128 --> 00:00:18.756
[Ransom] <i>Ben's not dead.
so his body is not in his grave.</i>

3
00:00:18.839 --> 00:00:20.215
There is something amiss.

4
00:00:20.299 --> 00:00:22.092
I am not the ninth Earl of Ellesmere.

5
00:00:22.176 --> 00:00:25.304
I've found myself wishing I could
renounce the title altogether.

6
00:00:25.387 --> 00:00:27.640
You could marry me
and give it to our firstborn.

7
00:00:27.723 --> 00:00:28.849
[Young Ian] Are you Denzell?

8
00:00:28.933 --> 00:00:30.601
- Heard you were a physician?
- I am.

9
00:00:30.684 --> 00:00:32.645
This is William Ransom. He's been injured.

10
00:00:32.728 --> 00:00:34.647
[Denny] Rachel!
These men need our assistance.

11
00:00:34.730 --> 00:00:36.065
My wife is in the city.

12
00:00:36.941 --> 00:00:38.150
I promised I'd return.

13
00:00:38.234 --> 00:00:40.736
I can find you a safe place
to wait out the battle.

14
00:00:40.819 --> 00:00:42.029
Unless you want to fight.

15
00:00:42.112 --> 00:00:43.072
I'm Aaron Whitaker.

16
00:00:43.155 --> 00:00:45.074
Allow my wife to help yours.

17
00:00:45.157 --> 00:00:48.244
May I introduce to you
William Buccleigh MacKenzie.

18
00:00:48.327 --> 00:00:49.662
The reputation precedes you.

19
00:00:49.745 --> 00:00:50.829
As does yours.

20
00:00:50.913 --> 00:00:52.790
A man being called by God is one thing.

21
00:00:52.873 --> 00:00:55.125
<i>A man who thinks
he cannot die is quite another.</i>

22
00:00:55.209 --> 00:00:57.086
You have men arming up under your nose.

23
00:00:57.169 --> 00:00:59.296
and you're too high-minded
to set an example?

24
00:00:59.380 --> 00:01:00.214
Well. I'm not.

25
00:01:11.934 --> 00:01:12.768
[Jamie] Mm.

26
00:01:13.686 --> 00:01:14.603
Ambrosia.

27
00:01:15.646 --> 00:01:17.189
- Mm.
- [bees buzzing]

28
00:01:17.982 --> 00:01:19.858
Anything you'd like to tell the bees?

29
00:01:20.859 --> 00:01:26.198
They didn't have much to offer me when I
told them that everyone had left us again.

30
00:01:28.951 --> 00:01:31.328
Well... Not everyone.

31
00:01:31.412 --> 00:01:33.455
[children chattering]

32
00:01:34.164 --> 00:01:34.999
Hmm.

33
00:01:37.626 --> 00:01:40.379
He promised to fight with me
at King's Mountain.

34
00:01:41.839 --> 00:01:44.049
You told him about it?

35
00:01:44.133 --> 00:01:46.176
He's one of you. Claire.

36
00:01:46.260 --> 00:01:48.804
Didn't see the purpose
in keeping it from him.

37
00:01:51.849 --> 00:01:52.808
You're it.

38
00:01:52.891 --> 00:01:54.852
He's been it more times than anyone.

39
00:01:54.935 --> 00:01:58.939
Did you tell him
that we killed his father?

40
00:02:00.649 --> 00:02:01.567
No.

41
00:02:02.568 --> 00:02:04.653
Nor did I tell him you killed his mother.

42
00:02:05.529 --> 00:02:06.405
Good.

43
00:02:07.489 --> 00:02:09.908
Let's keep that to ourselves. shall we?

44
00:02:11.452 --> 00:02:13.704
A tree or a wee mouse?

45
00:02:16.248 --> 00:02:17.499
Ah. fine.

46
00:02:18.751 --> 00:02:19.668
Thank you.

47
00:02:20.127 --> 00:02:22.254
- [twig snaps]
- [leaves rustling]

48
00:02:26.216 --> 00:02:29.053
- Go to the house. children.
- Is it a bear?

49
00:02:29.803 --> 00:02:30.846
I dinna ken.

50
00:02:32.014 --> 00:02:33.098
Go now.

51
00:02:33.349 --> 00:02:34.433
Go.

52
00:02:37.603 --> 00:02:38.520
Something's wrong.

53
00:02:44.401 --> 00:02:45.569
[man] Don't shoot.

54
00:02:48.530 --> 00:02:49.698
Buck!

55
00:02:49.782 --> 00:02:51.700
He was watching the house. You ken him?

56
00:02:51.784 --> 00:02:53.744
Aye. aye. I do.

57
00:02:53.827 --> 00:02:56.914
I don't think he's here to harm us.
Are you. Mr. Whitaker?

58
00:02:56.997 --> 00:02:59.249
No. sir. I'm not.

59
00:02:59.333 --> 00:03:01.460
Are you lurking about in the woods?

60
00:03:01.543 --> 00:03:05.172
Do you know a man named Cunningham.
Mr. Fraser?

61
00:03:05.255 --> 00:03:07.174
- A captain?
- Aye.

62
00:03:08.050 --> 00:03:09.426
He's coming for you.

63
00:03:13.305 --> 00:03:14.556
[theme music playing]

64
00:03:14.640 --> 00:03:16.225
<i>â™ª Sing me a song â™ª</i>

65
