<i>â™ª Of a lass that is gone â™ª</i>

80
00:04:15.909 --> 00:04:21.999
{\an8}<i>â™ª Say. could that lass be I? â™ª</i>

81
00:04:22.082 --> 00:04:24.710
<i>â™ª Merry of soul â™ª</i>

82
00:04:24.793 --> 00:04:28.297
{\an8}<i>â™ª She sailed on a day â™ª</i>

83
00:04:28.380 --> 00:04:35.345
{\an8}<i>â™ª Over the sea â™ª</i>

84
00:04:36.597 --> 00:04:43.562
{\an8}<i>â™ª To Skye â™ª</i>

85
00:05:09.087 --> 00:05:12.508
Uh. me and some of my men
were out hunting the Cherokee.

86
00:05:13.425 --> 00:05:15.177
While we was hunting. some white men

87
00:05:15.260 --> 00:05:17.387
hailed us and started
talking to the Cherokee

88
00:05:17.471 --> 00:05:20.891
about joining a Loyalist militia
that Cunningham's putting together.

89
00:05:20.974 --> 00:05:24.269
One of them let it be known
that this Cunningham

90
00:05:24.353 --> 00:05:26.813
would soon be in charge of Fraser's Ridge.

91
00:05:31.443 --> 00:05:32.486
Go on.

92
00:05:32.569 --> 00:05:34.947
They camped the night with us.

93
00:05:35.030 --> 00:05:36.907
My men and I. we daren't sleep.

94
00:05:37.824 --> 00:05:40.619
So. I listened.

95
00:05:41.453 --> 00:05:44.331
They said there's
a Red Coat officer named Ferguson.

96
00:05:45.040 --> 00:05:49.002
who's been raising Loyalist militias.
arresting rebels.

97
00:05:55.550 --> 00:05:57.386
I know about him.

98
00:05:57.469 --> 00:06:01.348
Well. Cunningham means to attack you
and take you to him...

99
00:06:03.642 --> 00:06:05.477
so he can hang you for sure.

100
00:06:07.980 --> 00:06:08.814
When?

101
00:06:08.897 --> 00:06:11.191
He said in a few days.

102
00:06:11.275 --> 00:06:13.527
Cunningham's waiting
on a fellow named Partland.

103
00:06:13.610 --> 00:06:17.197
who's coming from the settlement of 96
with a militia of his own to help him.

104
00:06:18.073 --> 00:06:20.409
He means to overpower you.

105
00:06:23.537 --> 00:06:25.497
You've done me a service. Mr. Whitaker.

106
00:06:27.749 --> 00:06:28.625
I'll remember it.

107
00:06:29.001 --> 00:06:30.460
The way I see it.

108
00:06:31.044 --> 00:06:33.380
I owe you for what your wife
did for my family.

109
00:06:34.715 --> 00:06:36.425
But if they find out I warned you...

110
00:06:36.508 --> 00:06:37.718
They won't find out.

111
00:06:38.802 --> 00:06:40.178
And you dinna owe me.

112
00:06:42.431 --> 00:06:44.516
But I'm grateful just the same.

113
00:07:05.662 --> 00:07:07.039
Am I interrupting?

114
00:07:07.122 --> 00:07:09.249
No. come in.

115
00:07:18.342 --> 00:07:19.635
[Amaranthus] How does it look?

116
00:07:19.718 --> 00:07:22.220
It looks very lovely.

117
00:07:24.348 --> 00:07:26.391
- [explosions in the distance]
- [baby fussing]

118
00:07:26.475 --> 00:07:29.061
- It is only the French ships.
- [Brianna] I know.

119
00:07:30.395 --> 00:07:32.939
But Lord John. he said
battle appears imminent.

120
00:07:33.023 --> 00:07:36.902
And without me knowing
exactly where my husband is...

121
00:07:39.279 --> 00:07:40.864
I really think I must feed him.

122
00:07:40.947 --> 00:07:43.200
That's fine. Lady Grey.
We can resume this afternoon.

123
00:07:55.295 --> 00:07:56.713
She is lovely. isn't she?

124
00:07:58.006 --> 00:08:00.384
Yes. I suppose she is.

125
00:08:02.094 --> 00:08:04.179
[Brianna] Sit down. keep me company.

126
00:08:07.849 --> 00:08:10.185
[explosions continue]

127
00:08:10.268 --> 00:08:12.729
You know. you don't have to do this.

128
00:08:14.064 --> 00:08:17.526
Everyone will understand if you put it off
until your husband returns.

129
00:08:18.193 --> 00:08:20.487
Honestly. it's helping me
keep my mind off of it.

130
00:08:20.570 --> 00:08:21.988
[chuckles softly]

131
00:08:25.826 --> 00:08:27.035
Can I ask you something?

132
00:08:28.286 --> 00:08:31.081
It's about Jamie. So. you can say no.

133
00:08:33.375 --> 00:08:37.504
Were you able to spend any time
with him... after you met?

134
00:08:38.422 --> 00:08:40.006
There was no occasion for that.

135
00:08:44.803 --> 00:08:47.347
Actually. that's not true.

136
00:08:47.431 --> 00:08:52.853
There was one occasion
when he helped me look for someone.

137
00:08:54.479 --> 00:08:55.689
Was that Jane?

138
00:08:57.315 --> 00:08:59.025
Fanny told me about her.

139
00:08:59.109 --> 00:09:01.278
I understand
she meant a great deal to you.

140
00:09:02.571 --> 00:09:03.447
She did.

141
00:09:05.198 --> 00:09:06.533
More than I ever told her.

142
00:09:10.036 --> 00:09:13.999
So. yes. to answer your question.
your father helped me and I was grateful.

143
00:09:15.083 --> 00:09:16.585
But that was the end of it.

144
00:09:16.668 --> 00:09:18.503
I do know how you feel.

145
00:09:18.587 --> 00:09:21.173
I didn't know he was
my father till I was 19.

146
00:09:22.966 --> 00:09:25.802
and I didn't meet him
until a few years after that.

147
00:09:27.387 --> 00:09:29.222
I already had a father I loved.

148
00:09:30.891 --> 00:09:32.642
Idolized. really.

149
00:09:35.437 --> 00:09:37.439
Though by then. he had died. which...

150
00:09:39.649 --> 00:09:42.235
made it worse somehow.

151
00:09:43.737 --> 00:09:44.738
I didn't know.

152
00:09:45.739 --> 00:09:48.241
Everyone had lied to me all my life.

153
00:09:49.242 --> 00:09:50.577
including my mother.

154
00:09:51.870 --> 00:09:56.249
And I just lost sense of who I was.

155
00:09:57.209 --> 00:09:59.377
I was so angry at her

156
00:10:00.420 --> 00:10:03.048
that I told her she was
the one who should have died.

157
00:10:05.467 --> 00:10:06.760
[sighs]

158
00:10:06.843 --> 00:10:08.178
Sound familiar?

159
00:10:10.430 --> 00:10:12.307
How did you overcome it?

160
00:10:12.390 --> 00:10:14.643
I got to know our father.

161
00:10:38.625 --> 00:10:42.796
- That bloody snake.
- Aye. That he is.

162
00:10:45.423 --> 00:10:48.677
He will not attack me here
when I have the advantage.

163
00:10:49.761 --> 00:10:51.346
He's canny.

164
00:10:51.429 --> 00:10:53.557
He'll have heard
how it went with Richard Brown.

165
00:10:54.933 --> 00:10:57.561
He'll wait for me to be somewhere
where he has the upper hand.

166
00:10:57.644 --> 00:11:00.480
So the... the trading post. then?

167
00:11:01.398 --> 00:11:02.482
Too crowded.

168
00:11:02.566 --> 00:11:05.235
He won't worry about keeping it quiet.

169
00:11:06.611 --> 00:11:10.198
It'll be Lodge. It's the perfect place
for a surprise attack.

170
00:11:10.282 --> 00:11:11.491
Why?

171
00:11:12.617 --> 00:11:13.994
I will not be armed. No one will.

172
00:11:15.745 --> 00:11:17.163
It's not allowed.

173
00:11:17.247 --> 00:11:18.290
[Claire] He'll be armed.

174
00:11:18.373 --> 00:11:22.210
- He won't care about what's allowed.
- Aye. He will care.

175
00:11:23.461 --> 00:11:25.964
Cunningham is a mason of the 25th degree.

176
00:11:26.047 --> 00:11:27.507
He takes his oath seriously.

177
00:11:29.009 --> 00:11:30.010
No.

178
00:11:31.303 --> 00:11:33.930
He will not start a fight inside.

179
00:11:34.014 --> 00:11:35.015
It'll be after.

180
00:11:35.807 --> 00:11:38.018
That's what I would do if I were him.

181
00:11:38.935 --> 00:11:41.187
- Then. don't go to Lodge.
- [Buck] Aye.

182
00:11:41.271 --> 00:11:42.814
Why not kill him now?

183
00:11:42.897 --> 00:11:46.359
He doesn't ken you've been warned.
and that gives you the advantage.

184
00:11:46.443 --> 00:11:48.486
We've to ken who else is with him.

185
00:11:48.570 --> 00:11:50.280
Not just Loyalists.

186
00:11:50.363 --> 00:11:53.283
Who among my tenants
would attack me on my own land?

187
00:11:53.366 --> 00:11:54.743
I have to go.

188
00:11:55.577 --> 00:11:58.330
With planning. I can handle Cunningham.

189
00:11:58.413 --> 00:12:03.084
but the problem is
the militia coming from 96.

190
00:12:03.168 --> 00:12:05.045
We have to cut it off.

191
00:12:05.128 --> 00:12:08.006
What about your militia?
The men you signed?

192
00:12:08.089 --> 00:12:11.593
They're untrained. unorganized.
spread across the county.

193
00:12:13.178 --> 00:12:16.306
No. there's only one way
I can see to stop it.

194
00:12:17.390 --> 00:12:18.767
I have to make a deal

195
00:12:19.809 --> 00:12:21.061
with the devil.

196
00:12:25.982 --> 00:12:27.859
Deliver it in person. Josiah.

197
00:12:27.942 --> 00:12:29.694
Aye. I'll ride all night.

198
00:12:43.208 --> 00:12:46.211
[Roger] <i>Dearest Bree. I'm sorry.</i>

199
00:12:46.670 --> 00:12:48.046
<i>I didn't mean to be here.</i>

200
00:12:48.922 --> 00:12:52.467
<i>but I have the strongest feeling
that here is where I'm supposed to be.</i>

201
00:12:53.843 --> 00:12:55.970
<i>It wasn't quite. "Whom shall I send."</i>

202
00:12:56.054 --> 00:12:58.139
<i>but something close.</i>

203
00:12:58.223 --> 00:13:00.350
<i>And so was my answer.</i>

204
00:13:00.433 --> 00:13:02.394
<i>That's Isaiah. if you don't know.</i>

205
00:13:02.477 --> 00:13:04.729
<i>Chapter 6. verse 8.</i>

206
00:13:05.772 --> 00:13:07.565
<i>"Here I am. Send me."</i>

207
00:13:09.234 --> 00:13:11.027
<i>I heard that call. too.</i>

208
00:13:11.111 --> 00:13:13.446
<i>How can I sit idly by watching men</i>

209
00:13:13.530 --> 00:13:15.865
<i>much younger than myself
prepare for battle</i>

210
00:13:15.949 --> 00:13:17.409
<i>I know they will lose?</i>

211
00:13:18.284 --> 00:13:22.080
<i>I think my father must have heard
the same call when he joined the RAF.</i>

212
00:13:22.747 --> 00:13:24.874
<i>I wonder if he was as scared as I am.</i>

213
00:13:26.042 --> 00:13:27.752
<i>God willing. I'll see you soon.</i>

214
00:13:28.628 --> 00:13:31.673
<i>God willing.
I'll see Jemmy and Mandy. too.</i>

215
00:13:31.756 --> 00:13:32.924
<i>I love you all.</i>

216
00:13:33.007 --> 00:13:36.302
<i>For now and always.
I am your husband. Roger.</i>

217
00:13:47.689 --> 00:13:49.649
[sighs] Lord. help me do
what you want me to do.

218
00:13:49.733 --> 00:13:51.025
whatever that is.

219
00:13:52.152 --> 00:13:55.447
In the name of Christ. your son.
let me live through it.

220
00:13:55.530 --> 00:13:58.408
Because if you don't.
you'll have my wife to answer to.

221
00:13:58.491 --> 00:14:00.577
- [man] Move it!
- [drum beating]

222
00:14:44.162 --> 00:14:45.747
It's going to be all right.

223
00:14:47.248 --> 00:14:50.251
Look. I'm scared. too. See?

224
00:14:52.212 --> 00:14:53.755
But. just remember.

225
00:14:54.464 --> 00:14:56.591
God is with us.

226
00:14:58.635 --> 00:15:00.011
[in French] Thank you. sir.

227
00:15:02.055 --> 00:15:03.264
Are you ready?

228
00:15:06.059 --> 00:15:07.560
I am ready.

229
00:15:07.644 --> 00:15:08.895
All right.

230
00:15:23.701 --> 00:15:26.162
[explosions in the distance]

231
00:15:28.248 --> 00:15:29.916
[sighs]

232
00:15:33.461 --> 00:15:35.255
[knock at door]

233
00:15:39.968 --> 00:15:41.594
That isn't the ships.

234
00:15:42.178 --> 00:15:43.513
No. it isn't.

235
00:15:46.766 --> 00:15:49.018
I'm afraid the battle has begun.

236
00:15:49.602 --> 00:15:52.564
They're attacking from the south.
through the marshes.

237
00:15:52.647 --> 00:15:55.233
which is not something
I personally would do.

238
00:15:55.316 --> 00:15:58.236
But styles of command vary.

239
00:16:01.030 --> 00:16:02.740
The only road into town is closed.

240
00:16:04.868 --> 00:16:08.580
If your husband hasn't returned by now.
it may be a while.

241
00:16:10.957 --> 00:16:13.334
What was it that took him out of town?

242
00:16:15.587 --> 00:16:17.130
[clears throat] It was. uh...

243
00:16:21.968 --> 00:16:23.761
He was at the continental camp.

244
00:16:24.637 --> 00:16:26.139
Why in God's name?

245
00:16:26.222 --> 00:16:29.684
He's a minister.
He was ministering to some of the men.

246
00:16:29.767 --> 00:16:32.562
Then. he'll be kept
well back from the front lines.

247
00:16:32.645 --> 00:16:34.230
He'll be safe.

248
00:16:34.731 --> 00:16:37.984
You know as well as I do
that being kept away from the front lines

249
00:16:38.067 --> 00:16:39.944
doesn't keep anyone safe.

250
00:16:42.197 --> 00:16:45.116
Oh. God! God. I hate this.

251
00:16:46.784 --> 00:16:48.828
[exhales deeply] Where is Lord John?

252
00:16:48.912 --> 00:16:50.705
At headquarters. trying to remember

253
00:16:50.788 --> 00:16:53.791
what a lieutenant colonel
is supposed to do.

254
00:16:53.875 --> 00:16:55.710
He's been retired for so long.

255
00:17:00.131 --> 00:17:02.175
He wanted you to have this.

256
00:17:06.262 --> 00:17:09.015
He's quite certain the rebels
will not breach the city.

257
00:17:10.808 --> 00:17:14.020
But if they should. and only if.

258
00:17:15.438 --> 00:17:19.108
we are to hang that in a window
so they know you're on their side.

259
00:17:20.485 --> 00:17:23.988
He'll deny all knowledge
of your radical affiliations. of course.

260
00:17:28.284 --> 00:17:30.912
- [explosions]
- [men grunting]

261
00:17:54.310 --> 00:17:57.355
Tell Mary I love her.

262
00:17:59.274 --> 00:18:00.817
I always did.

263
00:18:02.819 --> 00:18:04.237
Long before she knew.

264
00:18:05.613 --> 00:18:06.489
Tell her.

265
00:18:07.365 --> 00:18:08.449
Please tell her.

266
00:18:09.242 --> 00:18:10.243
I'll tell her.

267
00:18:15.623 --> 00:18:16.499
What's your name?

268
00:18:17.500 --> 00:18:18.626
Winslow.

269
00:18:19.335 --> 00:18:21.379
Private Winslow Carver.

270
00:18:26.050 --> 00:18:27.468
You're not alone. Winslow.

271
00:18:28.761 --> 00:18:30.054
Can you hear me?

272
00:18:30.138 --> 00:18:31.431
You're not alone.

273
00:18:32.390 --> 00:18:33.516
God is with you.

274
00:18:34.600 --> 00:18:35.852
And I'm with you. too.

275
00:18:37.270 --> 00:18:38.187
I won't leave you.

276
00:18:40.106 --> 00:18:41.816
[exhales deeply]

277
00:19:47.423 --> 00:19:49.425
[man muttering]

278
00:19:51.427 --> 00:19:54.097
[groaning]

279
00:19:54.180 --> 00:19:56.474
I'm here to help. I'm here to help.

280
00:19:57.225 --> 00:19:58.142
Doctor.

281
00:19:59.435 --> 00:20:01.187
- I need a doctor!
- Down there.

282
00:20:03.231 --> 00:20:04.440
[Denny] Bring him here.

283
00:20:05.525 --> 00:20:06.442
Lay him down.

284
00:20:09.237 --> 00:20:11.322
He's been shot through the neck. I think.

285
00:20:17.703 --> 00:20:18.579
Can thee hear me?

286
00:20:19.247 --> 00:20:20.164
Can thee breathe?

287
00:20:23.626 --> 00:20:24.710
[groans]

288
00:20:24.794 --> 00:20:26.796
Don't worry. I'm going to help thee.

289
00:20:35.388 --> 00:20:36.722
He can't die. Doctor.

290
00:20:37.432 --> 00:20:39.642
I told him that
it was going to be all right.

291
00:20:39.725 --> 00:20:41.436
I told him God was with us.

292
00:20:42.228 --> 00:20:43.146
He is.

293
00:20:48.317 --> 00:20:49.152
What am I doing?

294
00:20:57.702 --> 00:20:59.454
[in French] Pray for me.

295
00:21:00.163 --> 00:21:01.038
Pray?

296
00:21:02.498 --> 00:21:03.666
[in English] Yes. of course.

297
00:21:05.334 --> 00:21:08.379
Lord God. please heal my friend...

298
00:21:08.463 --> 00:21:10.465
[in French] Your name. What is your name?

299
00:21:11.132 --> 00:21:12.258
Christophe.

300
00:21:12.341 --> 00:21:13.759
Good day. Christophe.

301
00:21:13.843 --> 00:21:15.219
My name is Roger.

302
00:21:15.303 --> 00:21:16.596
[groaning]

303
00:21:16.679 --> 00:21:19.557
[Roger] Lord. please look
after my friend. Christophe.

304
00:21:19.640 --> 00:21:22.185
I beg you. Heal him.

305
00:21:22.268 --> 00:21:24.604
He's a good and courageous man.

306
00:21:27.356 --> 00:21:28.441
Christophe.

307
00:21:30.067 --> 00:21:32.195
- [in English] Is he...
- He's still breathing.

308
00:21:33.404 --> 00:21:35.531
Thankfully. it missed
the trachea and major arteries.

309
00:21:43.289 --> 00:21:44.624
We'd hardly begun.

310
00:21:46.959 --> 00:21:48.127
I'll go back.

311
00:21:48.753 --> 00:21:50.046
Thank you.

312
00:22:10.483 --> 00:22:11.859
I'll help you!

313
00:23:05.496 --> 00:23:08.040
I've sent Jemmy and Mandy
over to Lizzie's.

314
00:23:12.586 --> 00:23:14.088
Cunningham will not harm you.

315
00:23:14.171 --> 00:23:15.089
And the bairns.

316
00:23:15.923 --> 00:23:17.174
It's only me he wants.

317
00:23:19.176 --> 00:23:20.011
Well.

318
00:23:20.928 --> 00:23:23.222
I know where the guns are. just in case.

319
00:23:30.896 --> 00:23:32.023
How do I look?

320
00:23:38.279 --> 00:23:40.156
Like you'd scare the devil himself.

321
00:23:40.239 --> 00:23:41.949
I don't want to scare him. Claire.

322
00:23:42.825 --> 00:23:45.578
Tonight. I need the devil on my side.

323
00:23:47.788 --> 00:23:49.498
No word from Josiah. then?

324
00:23:50.833 --> 00:23:51.792
No.

325
00:23:56.380 --> 00:23:57.465
Don't go.

326
00:23:57.548 --> 00:23:58.883
I have to go. Claire.

327
00:24:00.009 --> 00:24:01.093
Dinna fash.

328
00:24:03.637 --> 00:24:04.889
We have a plan.

329
00:24:05.973 --> 00:24:06.891
Plans fail.

330
00:24:07.850 --> 00:24:09.393
That's why they call them plans.

331
00:24:10.895 --> 00:24:12.146
[Claire scoffs]

332
00:24:12.229 --> 00:24:13.397
There's even a saying.

333
00:24:15.149 --> 00:24:16.609
written by a Scot. no less.

334
00:24:19.320 --> 00:24:23.240
"The best-laid schemes
of mice and men gang aft agley."

335
00:24:25.534 --> 00:24:27.703
There's a play about it in my time.

336
00:24:28.704 --> 00:24:30.873
and things go very "agley."

337
00:24:31.999 --> 00:24:34.794
Cunningham doesn't want me dead.
only captured.

338
00:24:36.128 --> 00:24:38.130
He doesn't ken I know.

339
00:24:38.214 --> 00:24:40.966
My Ardsmuir men will be with me at Lodge.

340
00:24:41.050 --> 00:24:45.054
I have Buck and Kezzie
watching for the militia from 96.

341
00:24:46.222 --> 00:24:49.642
But if Josiah should fail
and the militia comes in...

342
00:24:49.725 --> 00:24:50.768
Then what?

343
00:24:56.690 --> 00:24:58.567
Then. I will fight. Claire.

344
00:24:59.527 --> 00:25:02.655
tooth and nail. and every man with me.

345
00:25:08.536 --> 00:25:10.329
It won't be today. will it?

346
00:25:10.413 --> 00:25:12.164
I don't think so. Claire.

347
00:25:14.917 --> 00:25:16.293
I will not lie to you.

348
00:25:17.628 --> 00:25:19.880
I think it will be an evil night.

349
00:25:32.143 --> 00:25:33.144
Mac Dubh.

350
00:25:33.227 --> 00:25:35.271
- Mac Dubh.
- Mac Dubh.

351
00:25:41.402 --> 00:25:43.320
[breathes deeply]

352
00:25:53.289 --> 00:25:55.291
Worshipful Master.

353
00:25:56.625 --> 00:25:58.002
Shall we begin?

354
00:26:41.712 --> 00:26:45.716
Let us invoke the assistance
of the great architect of the universe

355
00:26:45.799 --> 00:26:48.010
in all our undertakings.

356
00:26:49.470 --> 00:26:52.598
May our labors thus begun in order

357
00:26:52.681 --> 00:26:55.976
be conducted in peace.
enclosed in harmony.

358
00:26:56.060 --> 00:26:57.853
- So mote it be.
- So mote it be.

359
00:26:57.937 --> 00:27:01.690
I declare this Lodge duly open
for the purposes of Freemasonry.

360
00:27:02.399 --> 00:27:03.567
Is there any business?

361
00:27:04.276 --> 00:27:05.236
Aye.

362
00:27:06.111 --> 00:27:07.363
Brother Crombie.

363
00:27:11.450 --> 00:27:14.411
[Hiram] My nearest neighbor. Senga Argyle.

364
00:27:14.495 --> 00:27:17.456
is a recent widow. and none too spry.

365
00:27:17.540 --> 00:27:21.293
She does not have kin.
And as an elderly woman.

366
00:27:21.377 --> 00:27:24.129
lacks the means to maintain her land.

367
00:27:24.213 --> 00:27:26.840
The poor woman cannot care
for her late husband's stock.

368
00:27:26.924 --> 00:27:31.637
and I can only offer her so much help.
busy as I am with the trading post.

369
00:27:31.720 --> 00:27:34.890
I cannot neglect the business
for hours on end.

370
00:27:34.974 --> 00:27:36.892
The Ridge would come to a standstill.

371
00:27:36.976 --> 00:27:40.020
So. if there be any man
lives east of the mill road

372
00:27:40.104 --> 00:27:42.439
who could see his way to helping me.

373
00:27:43.399 --> 00:27:44.692
it would be helping her.

374
00:27:44.775 --> 00:27:46.527
That'll be me. Brother Crombie.

375
00:27:46.610 --> 00:27:47.820
I live near enough.

376
00:27:56.453 --> 00:27:57.288
Anyone else?

377
00:27:58.247 --> 00:27:59.456
Aye.

378
00:28:02.751 --> 00:28:05.504
I'm in a dispute
with my neighbor. John Coyne.

379
00:28:05.588 --> 00:28:07.965
He's using my well. taking my water.

380
00:28:08.048 --> 00:28:10.509
I'd like someone to talk to him with me.

381
00:28:10.593 --> 00:28:12.469
I'll go with you. Brother McLure.

382
00:28:12.553 --> 00:28:14.138
You're his friend.

383
00:28:14.221 --> 00:28:17.558
That's just as well.
But I want someone on my behalf then. too.

384
00:28:18.309 --> 00:28:19.184
I'll go.

385
00:28:20.352 --> 00:28:23.647
If it's agreeable with you.
Worshipful Master.

386
00:28:24.815 --> 00:28:26.108
Aye.

387
00:28:26.191 --> 00:28:30.446
Tomorrow. at noon. shall we say?
I have no other plans.

388
00:28:42.541 --> 00:28:44.627
- I had to come.
- I know.

389
00:28:46.629 --> 00:28:48.172
You know?

390
00:28:48.839 --> 00:28:50.215
We know everything.

391
00:28:51.884 --> 00:28:55.679
Jamie knows the Captain
doesn't mean him immediate harm.

392
00:28:56.889 --> 00:28:58.724
He won't kill your son.

393
00:28:58.807 --> 00:29:00.267
Unless he has to.

394
00:29:04.396 --> 00:29:06.523
Let me offer you the same assurance.

395
00:29:13.614 --> 00:29:15.908
Nothing left for us to do now. is there?

396
00:29:17.117 --> 00:29:18.327
Actually.

397
00:29:19.787 --> 00:29:21.872
I thought we might pray.

398
00:29:21.956 --> 00:29:24.875
Do you know any prayers
suitable to the occasion?

399
00:29:29.797 --> 00:29:32.257
Is there anything else
before we start the beer?

400
00:29:32.341 --> 00:29:33.550
Yes.

401
00:29:33.634 --> 00:29:35.594
I'd like to say a few words. if I may.

402
00:29:37.763 --> 00:29:39.807
About loyalty.

403
00:29:44.311 --> 00:29:47.439
I shared with you before about my son.

404
00:29:47.523 --> 00:29:48.565
He was loyal.

405
00:29:49.525 --> 00:29:53.654
To me. as a father and as a commander.

406
00:29:53.737 --> 00:29:57.324
To his grandmother.
who helped me raise him.

407
00:29:57.408 --> 00:29:59.410
And to his king and country.

408
00:29:59.493 --> 00:30:03.789
Most especially. he was loyal unto death.

409
00:30:03.872 --> 00:30:05.791
as we all must be.

410
00:30:08.293 --> 00:30:10.045
Or it is not loyalty.

411
00:30:10.129 --> 00:30:13.132
What brings this to mind.
Brother Cunningham?

412
00:30:14.091 --> 00:30:18.303
The war is heavy on my heart. I'll admit.

413
00:30:18.387 --> 00:30:21.557
and I know we're not to speak
of politics in Lodge.

414
00:30:21.640 --> 00:30:23.976
- but...
- But since you have. so shall I.

415
00:30:25.769 --> 00:30:29.857
And I will say but one thing.
<i>a charaidean.</i> that is not mine own.

416
00:30:29.940 --> 00:30:33.318
but a thing said by our forefathers
some 400 years ago.

417
00:30:34.319 --> 00:30:37.865
"As long as
but a hundred of us remain alive.

418
00:30:38.907 --> 00:30:43.662
never shall we. on any conditions
be brought under English rule."

419
00:30:46.206 --> 00:30:47.499
"For it is in truth.

420
00:30:48.083 --> 00:30:51.462
not for glory. nor riches.

421
00:30:51.545 --> 00:30:53.630
nor honors that we are fighting.

422
00:30:54.965 --> 00:30:56.216
but for freedom."

423
00:30:58.052 --> 00:30:59.344
"For that alone.

424
00:31:01.597 --> 00:31:06.977
which no honest man gives up
but with life itself."

425
00:31:10.481 --> 00:31:13.025
Bow your heads with me
for the closing prayer.

426
00:31:13.108 --> 00:31:14.109
Brother Lindsay.

427
00:31:19.948 --> 00:31:23.202
Supreme grandmaster.
ruler of Heaven and Earth.

428
00:31:23.285 --> 00:31:26.497
Now that we are to separate and return

429
00:31:26.580 --> 00:31:29.374
to our respective places of abode.

430
00:31:29.458 --> 00:31:33.087
wilt thou be pleased
to influence our hearts and minds

431
00:31:33.170 --> 00:31:35.756
so that we may. each one of us.

432
00:31:35.839 --> 00:31:39.968
practice out of the Lodge
those great moral duties.

433
00:31:40.052 --> 00:31:41.678
which are inculcated in it.

434
00:31:41.762 --> 00:31:45.516
and with reverence.
study and obey the laws

435
00:31:45.599 --> 00:31:49.311
which thou hast given to us
in thy holy word.

436
00:31:49.394 --> 00:31:50.437
Amen.

437
00:31:50.521 --> 00:31:52.397
- So mote it be.
- So mote it be.

438
00:31:52.481 --> 00:31:53.899
God damn it.

439
00:31:59.905 --> 00:32:02.908
God damn you for a plague of rats!

440
00:32:02.991 --> 00:32:04.118
Where is he?

441
00:32:16.421 --> 00:32:17.381
[whistles]

442
00:32:27.683 --> 00:32:29.601
Any sign of those bastards from 96?

443
00:32:29.685 --> 00:32:30.769
Not yet.

444
00:32:30.853 --> 00:32:33.105
Josiah has not come back either.

445
00:32:33.188 --> 00:32:35.899
- My brother will not let you down.
- Thank you. Kezzie.

446
00:32:37.901 --> 00:32:41.738
Geordie Hallam. Conor MacNeil.
Lachlan Hunt. Ewan Adair.

447
00:32:41.822 --> 00:32:46.034
- There were more behind us. but...
- Holman Leslie. Robert McClanahan.

448
00:32:46.118 --> 00:32:49.079
William Baird. Joseph Baird.
Hiram Crombie.

449
00:32:49.746 --> 00:32:51.081
And more yet behind them.

450
00:32:51.623 --> 00:32:53.167
Friends and neighbors. all.

451
00:32:53.250 --> 00:32:55.335
"Peace and harmony." they quoted just now.

452
00:32:55.419 --> 00:32:56.962
while lying in wait. forbye.

453
00:32:57.045 --> 00:32:58.297
Draw them into the trees.

454
00:32:58.380 --> 00:33:00.382
Mark their names
and capture those you can.

455
00:33:00.465 --> 00:33:03.010
Any man in these woods is a traitor to me.

456
00:33:03.093 --> 00:33:06.054
But dinna shoot to kill.
Cunningham wants me alive.

457
00:33:06.138 --> 00:33:09.224
I'll not be the one
who brings death here tonight.

458
00:33:09.308 --> 00:33:12.978
[thunder rumbling]

459
00:33:18.025 --> 00:33:20.027
The storm will be here soon.

460
00:33:23.530 --> 00:33:24.781
Where are the children?

461
00:33:26.700 --> 00:33:28.118
Away for the night.

462
00:33:29.745 --> 00:33:31.038
And Fanny's asleep.

463
00:33:42.216 --> 00:33:43.467
What are you thinking?

464
00:33:45.385 --> 00:33:47.137
Five more years.

465
00:33:47.221 --> 00:33:48.597
I'm sorry?

466
00:33:49.306 --> 00:33:52.768
When my grandson died.
that was two years ago.

467
00:33:52.851 --> 00:33:54.394
So. you do believe it.

468
00:33:55.896 --> 00:33:59.483
"I'll see you again in seven years."
Five more left.

469
00:34:01.151 --> 00:34:04.613
It doesn't mean
that my son will kill your husband.

470
00:34:04.696 --> 00:34:08.825
It only means that
your husband will not kill him.

471
00:34:13.997 --> 00:34:18.210
That must be a comfort to you.

472
00:34:22.589 --> 00:34:25.133
He only intends to take him
to Patrick Ferguson...

473
00:34:25.217 --> 00:34:26.551
To be hanged...

474
00:34:27.552 --> 00:34:29.805
for the sake
of his own bloody advancement.

475
00:34:29.888 --> 00:34:31.431
For the sake of his king.

476
00:34:32.432 --> 00:34:34.851
and his honor as an officer of that king.

477
00:34:36.770 --> 00:34:38.563
Your husband is a pardoned traitor.

478
00:34:38.647 --> 00:34:40.816
He has forfeited the grace of that pardon.

479
00:34:40.899 --> 00:34:43.527
He has earned his own execution.

480
00:34:54.246 --> 00:34:55.080
[sighs]

481
00:34:56.581 --> 00:34:58.292
We were going to pray. weren't we?

482
00:35:09.886 --> 00:35:10.721
[thunderclap]

483
00:35:21.148 --> 00:35:22.899
- [gun cocks]
- [gasps]

484
00:35:24.192 --> 00:35:27.070
Don't say a word.

485
00:35:28.780 --> 00:35:30.198
Mr. Fraser. I can... [grunts]

486
00:36:06.401 --> 00:36:08.028
[Cunningham] Mr. Fraser.

487
00:36:09.321 --> 00:36:12.532
Let's talk this through. shall we?

488
00:36:13.450 --> 00:36:14.326
Man to man.

489
00:36:15.744 --> 00:36:17.204
I'm going to put my gun down.

490
00:36:22.918 --> 00:36:24.336
Not much to talk about.

491
00:36:25.837 --> 00:36:27.756
Save you leaving my land.

492
00:36:29.800 --> 00:36:32.803
On foot or in a box is up to you.

493
00:36:34.304 --> 00:36:36.598
But you forget. Mr. Fraser.

494
00:36:36.681 --> 00:36:38.725
I have a box waiting for me.

495
00:36:40.310 --> 00:36:41.770
but not for five more years.

496
00:36:45.774 --> 00:36:47.651
[both grunting]

497
00:36:56.868 --> 00:36:58.829
[Jamie screaming]

498
00:37:02.499 --> 00:37:03.500
[Cunningham grunts]

499
00:37:09.631 --> 00:37:11.758
[Jamie grunting]

500
00:37:15.971 --> 00:37:17.722
[thunderclap]

501
00:37:21.560 --> 00:37:23.145
[Cunningham groaning]

502
00:37:26.690 --> 00:37:28.066
[groans]

503
00:37:58.305 --> 00:37:59.806
How did you know it was coming?

504
00:38:00.223 --> 00:38:02.559
It's my ridge. I ken everything.

505
00:38:04.102 --> 00:38:07.355
I ken you mean to hand me over
to Ferguson to be hanged.

506
00:38:07.439 --> 00:38:08.815
That was the plan.

507
00:38:10.233 --> 00:38:11.735
but plans change!

508
00:38:12.235 --> 00:38:15.822
Aye. that's why they call them plans.

509
00:38:16.573 --> 00:38:18.867
Ferguson will take you alive or dead.

510
00:38:19.784 --> 00:38:21.036
At this point.

511
00:38:22.287 --> 00:38:24.706
I'm thinking dead
might save me a lot of bother.

512
00:38:30.420 --> 00:38:33.715
I never wanted it
to come to this. Mr. Fraser.

513
00:38:36.259 --> 00:38:37.260
[gunshot]

514
00:38:38.303 --> 00:38:39.638
[Cunningham thuds]

515
00:38:46.686 --> 00:38:48.438
[sighs in relief]

516
00:38:59.157 --> 00:39:02.452
My father has written to his counterpart
of the continental camp.

517
00:39:04.746 --> 00:39:07.332
With any luck.
we'll hear something in a day or two.

518
00:39:09.876 --> 00:39:10.710
No.

519
00:39:11.920 --> 00:39:13.505
The battle is over.

520
00:39:13.588 --> 00:39:17.008
and sitting here
waiting for news is unbearable.

521
00:39:20.428 --> 00:39:22.556
I need to see what's happening for myself.

522
00:39:24.766 --> 00:39:26.101
I'm going to the camp.

523
00:39:30.689 --> 00:39:32.315
If you are determined to go.

524
00:39:33.525 --> 00:39:34.901
then I will accompany you

525
00:39:35.652 --> 00:39:37.153
at first light.

526
00:39:42.242 --> 00:39:45.620
[thunder rumbling]

527
00:39:57.382 --> 00:39:58.383
[door opens]

528
00:40:05.015 --> 00:40:06.182
[Buck] We need you. Claire!

529
00:40:09.019 --> 00:40:11.646
Lift. lift! Here you go! Right here.

530
00:40:13.565 --> 00:40:14.649
Charlie...

531
00:40:15.609 --> 00:40:17.986
- Where's Jamie?
- Here. Sassenach.

532
00:40:18.069 --> 00:40:20.030
- Are you hurt?
- I'll bide.

533
00:40:20.113 --> 00:40:23.116
It's him. He's been shot in the back.

534
00:40:23.199 --> 00:40:26.286
Shot in the back? You coward!

535
00:40:26.369 --> 00:40:29.289
- Restrain yourself!
- He had no intention of killing you.

536
00:40:29.748 --> 00:40:32.334
You can ask your son
what his intentions were.

537
00:40:35.211 --> 00:40:36.338
- Let me see.
- [Jamie grunts]

538
00:40:37.255 --> 00:40:39.507
Looks like your clothes
took the worst of it.

539
00:40:41.676 --> 00:40:45.055
Go find Fanny. Tell her to clean the wound
and put a compress on it.

540
00:40:46.097 --> 00:40:47.599
You two. I'm going to need your help.

541
00:40:48.308 --> 00:40:50.727
Mr. Cunningham. where were you shot?

542
00:40:50.810 --> 00:40:53.104
- High or low?
- Low.

543
00:40:54.147 --> 00:40:55.523
Wiggle your fingers.

544
00:40:57.359 --> 00:40:59.527
All right. Good. Now. move your feet.

545
00:41:07.994 --> 00:41:10.538
Move your feet. Charlie. Up and down.

546
00:41:10.622 --> 00:41:12.290
I am. Mother!

547
00:41:12.374 --> 00:41:16.670
All right. There it is. between L3 and L4.

548
00:41:17.504 --> 00:41:19.714
Buck. Tom. help me roll him.

549
00:41:20.590 --> 00:41:24.427
- Towards you. Okay. Slowly.
- [Cunningham groaning]

550
00:41:25.804 --> 00:41:27.263
Okay. hold him steady.

551
00:41:30.642 --> 00:41:33.228
Mr. Fraser has a bad cut across his chest.

552
00:41:33.311 --> 00:41:35.271
It's just missed his left nipple.

553
00:41:35.355 --> 00:41:36.690
That's a bit of good news.

554
00:41:36.773 --> 00:41:38.483
- Did you...
- I put a compress on it.

555
00:41:38.566 --> 00:41:41.736
- How fast is the blood soaking through?
- Not too fast.

556
00:41:41.820 --> 00:41:43.780
He wants whiskey. Is that all right?

557
00:41:43.863 --> 00:41:47.200
Tell him if he can stand up
and count to 30. then he can have whiskey.

558
00:41:47.283 --> 00:41:49.994
If not. give him honey water
and make him lie down.

559
00:41:50.078 --> 00:41:51.204
no matter what he says.

560
00:41:51.287 --> 00:41:53.498
I've already given him honey water.

561
00:41:53.581 --> 00:41:55.375
Should the Captain have some. too?

562
00:41:56.459 --> 00:41:59.587
Yes. please. Thank you.

563
00:42:09.723 --> 00:42:12.892
Will he live? Tell me the truth.

564
00:42:14.811 --> 00:42:15.854
I think so.

565
00:42:17.981 --> 00:42:19.858
But he might not be able to walk.

566
00:42:21.151 --> 00:42:23.194
The ball didn't go all the way through.

567
00:42:23.653 --> 00:42:25.113
so it might heal.

568
00:42:25.822 --> 00:42:26.823
Or it might not.

569
00:42:30.410 --> 00:42:33.037
I'm going to remove the ball.
dress the wound.

570
00:42:35.790 --> 00:42:36.750
You should stay.

571
00:42:37.500 --> 00:42:39.961
It won't take long.
and I'll need your help.

572
00:42:47.427 --> 00:42:48.511
Hold him steady.

573
00:42:52.474 --> 00:42:54.851
[screaming]

574
00:43:14.287 --> 00:43:15.413
Trevor's sleeping.

575
00:43:17.207 --> 00:43:20.168
The surcease of cannon fire
is a boon to mothers.

576
00:43:20.251 --> 00:43:21.795
And to soldiers.

577
00:43:22.796 --> 00:43:26.049
Yes. Them. too.

578
00:43:32.430 --> 00:43:33.723
It's nice to see you.

579
00:43:34.724 --> 00:43:37.477
You've been rather busy today.
understandably.

580
00:43:40.980 --> 00:43:44.734
I should like to see you
in my beetle waistcoat again.

581
00:43:46.319 --> 00:43:48.822
Now. I believe there are
certain species I had not...

582
00:43:50.490 --> 00:43:52.992
touched on. taxonomically.

583
00:43:54.619 --> 00:43:58.832
The fiery searcher. the twice daft lady.

584
00:43:58.915 --> 00:44:00.041
Amaranthus. I...

585
00:44:04.045 --> 00:44:05.463
I must confess.

586
00:44:06.631 --> 00:44:11.761
I've developed a particular
species of feeling for you.

587
00:44:14.347 --> 00:44:15.640
[chuckles]

588
00:44:17.517 --> 00:44:20.520
That was a terrible attempt
at cleverness. I must say.

589
00:44:20.603 --> 00:44:22.188
I shan't try it again.

590
00:44:22.856 --> 00:44:24.023
On my honor.

591
00:44:26.025 --> 00:44:27.110
What are you saying?

592
00:44:29.946 --> 00:44:32.740
We both know how quickly
one can lose someone in war.

593
00:44:35.034 --> 00:44:37.662
I don't want things
to remain unsaid between us.

594
00:44:39.622 --> 00:44:42.792
I think you may have been jesting
when you suggested it. But...

595
00:44:43.918 --> 00:44:46.254
I have been thinking about your idea.

596
00:44:47.088 --> 00:44:48.298
Remind me.

597
00:44:49.549 --> 00:44:50.884
what was my idea?

598
00:44:51.426 --> 00:44:52.802
That we should get married.

599
00:44:54.053 --> 00:44:57.765
And if we should have a son.
I could give him my title.

600
00:44:59.267 --> 00:45:00.852
I wasn't jesting.

601
00:45:03.730 --> 00:45:05.607
But we needn't get married either.

602
00:45:06.441 --> 00:45:07.942
Not straightaway.

603
00:45:09.110 --> 00:45:10.695
We could...

604
00:45:12.280 --> 00:45:13.948
give it a go.

605
00:45:15.033 --> 00:45:16.701
And if the result is male...

606
00:45:16.784 --> 00:45:18.911
I don't believe
I'm having this conversation.

607
00:45:19.829 --> 00:45:21.748
And what the devil do you propose to do

608
00:45:21.831 --> 00:45:26.002
if this result. as you so
casually put it. is female?

609
00:45:26.085 --> 00:45:29.547
I suppose you'd have
to marry me in either case. eventually.

610
00:45:29.631 --> 00:45:31.883
Of course.
I might not get with child at all.

611
00:45:33.426 --> 00:45:35.470
We might just enjoy the try.

612
00:45:52.111 --> 00:45:53.655
It cannot be like this.

613
00:45:55.114 --> 00:45:56.074
No.

614
00:45:58.034 --> 00:45:59.661
No. I suppose it can't.

615
00:46:06.542 --> 00:46:09.754
On your honor. as you say.

616
00:46:17.720 --> 00:46:21.015
We will get married.
That is what we'll do.

617
00:46:34.779 --> 00:46:36.072
[Amaranthus moans]

618
00:46:38.533 --> 00:46:39.492
I accept.

619
00:47:10.148 --> 00:47:14.360
[Roger] For as much as it hath pleased
God Almighty to take unto himself

620
00:47:14.444 --> 00:47:17.530
the souls of these. our brothers.

621
00:47:17.613 --> 00:47:21.075
we therefore commit
their bodies to the ground.

622
00:47:21.159 --> 00:47:24.620
earth to earth.
ashes to ashes. dust to dust.

623
00:47:24.704 --> 00:47:29.208
in sure and certain hope
of resurrection to eternal life

624
00:47:29.292 --> 00:47:31.836
through our Lord. Jesus Christ.

625
00:47:31.919 --> 00:47:33.004
Amen.

626
00:47:41.554 --> 00:47:43.347
Please excuse me.

627
00:47:48.311 --> 00:47:49.562
[Brianna] Oh. my God.

628
00:48:01.324 --> 00:48:02.450
Oh. God.

629
00:48:03.367 --> 00:48:04.827
Are you hurt? Are you in pain?

630
00:48:04.911 --> 00:48:06.078
I'm fine.

631
00:48:07.121 --> 00:48:08.623
Minor explosion.

632
00:48:10.082 --> 00:48:12.877
You scared the shit out of me. Roger.
I thought you were dead.

633
00:48:12.960 --> 00:48:15.505
I know. I know. I'm sorry.

634
00:48:16.547 --> 00:48:17.673
I'm sorry.

635
00:48:19.342 --> 00:48:20.551
I wanted to...

636
00:48:23.429 --> 00:48:24.639
I couldn't leave.

637
00:48:27.892 --> 00:48:29.101
[Denny] How is thy knee?

638
00:48:29.602 --> 00:48:30.728
Not bad. Doctor.

639
00:48:32.438 --> 00:48:33.439
How's Christophe?

640
00:48:33.856 --> 00:48:34.941
He's doing well.

641
00:48:37.026 --> 00:48:40.988
Uh. Bree. I want you to meet
Dr. Denzell Hunter.

642
00:48:42.615 --> 00:48:45.952
That's right. That Denzell Hunter.
Rachel's brother.

643
00:48:46.035 --> 00:48:48.454
We just figured it out this morning.

644
00:48:49.455 --> 00:48:50.790
I'm so glad to meet you.

645
00:48:50.873 --> 00:48:52.124
And I thee.

646
00:48:53.084 --> 00:48:55.127
I wish it were in better circumstances.

647
00:48:56.921 --> 00:48:58.714
I know thy mother and father well.

648
00:48:59.549 --> 00:49:01.175
He knows me. too.

649
00:49:03.469 --> 00:49:04.387
William.

650
00:49:07.181 --> 00:49:08.099
William?

651
00:49:13.813 --> 00:49:17.567
I think I shall stay a while.
I'd not imagined I'd see Denzell again.

652
00:49:18.276 --> 00:49:19.318
Now that I have...

653
00:49:19.402 --> 00:49:22.446
You know. for a Loyalist.
you sure have a lot of rebel friends.

654
00:49:25.074 --> 00:49:26.742
I should go back to Savannah.

655
00:49:26.826 --> 00:49:29.912
My father's letter will still
grant you safe passage.

656
00:49:30.413 --> 00:49:32.540
Get him cleaned up and fed. And drunk.

657
00:49:42.550 --> 00:49:44.719
When did you last see your sister?

658
00:49:44.802 --> 00:49:47.346
Not since Monmouth.
But she's written to me.

659
00:49:48.180 --> 00:49:49.098
She had a baby.

660
00:49:50.600 --> 00:49:52.018
I think she's very happy.

661
00:49:54.437 --> 00:49:57.481
William. I know there was once
some trouble between me and Ian...

662
00:49:57.565 --> 00:49:59.358
I am very glad for them.

663
00:49:59.442 --> 00:50:01.152
Truly.

664
00:50:03.696 --> 00:50:04.780
I won't be a moment.

665
00:50:06.741 --> 00:50:08.159
I have a list of casualties...

666
00:50:16.292 --> 00:50:17.710
[exhales deeply]

667
00:50:20.046 --> 00:50:21.047
[man] Thank you. Doctor.

668
00:50:22.214 --> 00:50:23.132
Sad day. indeed.

669
00:50:26.928 --> 00:50:28.429
How in God's name?

670
00:50:28.512 --> 00:50:30.765
- Oh. this is...
- Dr. Hunter.

671
00:50:31.474 --> 00:50:33.643
could you give me a moment
with an old friend?

672
00:50:34.727 --> 00:50:36.771
I... Of course.

673
00:50:39.065 --> 00:50:40.274
I'll just be over there.

674
00:50:42.860 --> 00:50:43.778
Come inside.

675
00:50:57.333 --> 00:50:58.417
Ben.

676
00:51:09.428 --> 00:51:10.513
Hello. cousin.

677
00:51:14.976 --> 00:51:16.185
You son of a bitch.

678
00:51:21.440 --> 00:51:22.900
How's the eye?

679
00:51:33.619 --> 00:51:34.996
Why was Elspeth here?

680
00:51:35.788 --> 00:51:37.999
She came to pray with me.
believe it or not.

681
00:51:40.501 --> 00:51:42.420
She was as scared as I was.

682
00:51:44.547 --> 00:51:46.799
I was sure that it was
you in that stretcher.

683
00:51:49.552 --> 00:51:51.137
Almost was.

684
00:51:51.971 --> 00:51:53.556
I thought I was done for.

685
00:51:53.639 --> 00:51:58.561
Did not realize it was Buck's gun I heard
until I saw Cunningham fall.

686
00:52:04.942 --> 00:52:07.028
What happened to Cunningham's other men?

687
00:52:08.320 --> 00:52:09.905
Nought to fear from them.

688
00:52:09.989 --> 00:52:12.324
They were deprived
of their weapons and sent home.

689
00:52:12.408 --> 00:52:14.368
feeling a good deal
less brave about themselves.

690
00:52:17.455 --> 00:52:18.998
Do you have a piece of paper?

691
00:52:20.958 --> 00:52:21.876
Of course.

692
00:52:23.044 --> 00:52:24.003
Why?

693
00:52:25.796 --> 00:52:27.256
Write down these names.

694
00:52:28.174 --> 00:52:32.511
Geordie Hallam. Conor MacNeil.
Lachlan Hunt. Holman Leslie.

695
00:52:33.637 --> 00:52:34.472
Hiram Crombie.

696
00:52:34.555 --> 00:52:37.725
Why do you need me to write the list
when you remember who they are?

697
00:52:37.808 --> 00:52:40.186
The list is not for me. It's for you.

698
00:52:40.269 --> 00:52:43.022
If I'm not around.
you need to get rid of them.

699
00:52:43.105 --> 00:52:44.106
Get rid of them?

700
00:52:44.190 --> 00:52:47.276
I don't intend to keep them on as tenants.

701
00:52:48.027 --> 00:52:49.028
Tried to kill me.

702
00:52:49.862 --> 00:52:51.739
or send me away to be hanged.

703
00:52:51.822 --> 00:52:52.865
Which is no better.

704
00:52:52.948 --> 00:52:55.743
Someone's coming.
Ten men. at least. maybe more.

705
00:53:02.166 --> 00:53:03.751
[exhales deeply]

706
00:53:25.106 --> 00:53:26.816
Hello. the house!

707
00:53:39.662 --> 00:53:40.663
Sorry we're late.

708
00:53:40.746 --> 00:53:42.164
Glad you're here.

709
00:53:45.668 --> 00:53:47.670
I didn't think you'd come.

710
00:53:48.254 --> 00:53:50.714
Well. I almost didn't.

711
00:53:53.509 --> 00:53:57.680
There's only so many times
a man can have his help rebuffed

712
00:53:57.763 --> 00:53:59.557
before he starts feeling unhelpful.

713
00:54:00.558 --> 00:54:04.436
Then again. I can't generally
resist a fight with some Tories.

714
00:54:07.731 --> 00:54:08.816
We should talk.

715
00:54:09.567 --> 00:54:12.361
I have heard good things
about your whiskey.

716
00:54:13.946 --> 00:54:15.447
Why don't you pour me some?

717
00:54:24.999 --> 00:54:28.002
Send for the devil. the devil appears.
